text: T. australis may refer to: * Tadarida australis, the white-striped free-tailed bat, a bat species found in Australia, Indonesia and Papua New Guinea * Telmatobufo australis, a frog species endemic to Chile * Terminalia australis, a large shrub or tree species found in Argentina, Paraguay and Uruguay * Treron australis, a pigeon ==See also== * Australis (disambiguation)
title: T. australis
